<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB01031</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR A COMPREHENSIVE NUCLEAR REGULATION, CREATING FOR THE PURPOSE, THE PHILIPPINE NUCLEAR REGULATORY COMMISSION, AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Aims to create a single, independent nuclear regulatory body for implementing effective measures to control, prevent, detect uses and application of nuclear energy and respond to unauthorized acts involving nuclear material, other radioactive sources or associated facilities that may cause injury to persons, property or the environment or jeopardize national security.</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ALIAS NAME : “Comprehensive Nuclear Regulation Act of 2019.”</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>SALCEDA, JOEY SARTE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-07-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Cabredo (000 2019-07-24)</td><td>2. Jalosjos (000 2019-08-01)</td><tr><td>3. Albano (A.) (000 2019-08-05)</td><td>4. Umali (M.V.) (000 2019-08-08)</td><tr><td>5. Bustos (000 2019-08-13)</td><td>6. Nieto (000 2019-08-14)</td><tr><td>7. Del Mar (000 2019-08-20)</td><td>8. Acosta (000 2019-08-20)</td><tr><td>9. Violago (000 2019-08-22)</td><td>10. Delos Santos (000 2019-08-27)</td><tr><td>11. Castro (F.H.) (000 2019-08-27)</td><td>12. Lacson (000 2019-09-10)</td><tr><td>13. Aumentado (000 2019-09-10)</td><td>14. Ebcas (000 2019-09-23)</td><tr><td>15. Garin (S.) (000 2019-09-23)</td><td>16. Kho (W.) (000 2019-09-23)</td><tr><td>17. Savellano (000 2019-10-09)</td><td>18. Vargas (000 2020-02-17)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON GOVERNMENT REORGANIZATION ON 2019-11-26</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMI